[[!meta title="Energy Drink — Gorilla Mind Wild Grape"]]
[[!tag Energy_Drink Review]]

Gorilla Mind is a weird brand. I found mine at an [[Exxon]] that recently
started stocking them near me. My gym also stocks them. The reason they are
called Gorilla _Mind_ (they sell Gorilla Dream and other things prefixed with
"Gorilla") is because of the blended Gorilla Mind Energy Matrix, a purported
nootropic stack of (quote):

- N-Acetyl-L-Tyrosine
- Alpha-GPC 50%
- Caffeine
- Uridine 5'-Monophosphate
- L-Theanine
- Huperzine A
- Saffron extract

Not sure about all that!

I've tried [[Gorilla_Mind_Arctic_White]] a bit over a year ago. Today I've found
Wild Grape. I do not seek out Gorilla Mind. It seeks me.

<figure>
[[!template id="hooya-img.tmpl" cid="bafkreihx4tzbdoswodqbugdjbdjbhw5qkwlsiuonxjoti4hmvkpzkc7l5a" size=medium]]
</figure>

Gorilla Mind Wild Grape is an artificial grape flavor like any other. Intense
carbonation gives it a unique velvet-y texture. Otherwise the taste of this
drink is nothing remarkable. Flavor is exactly like [[Rip_It_G-Force]].

This drink did make me feel funny, I did not notice with
[[Gorilla_Mind_Arctic_White]] but maybe because I was moving around. Trying to
sit still was hard. I lost focus a number of times writing this. It might also
be the caffeine paired with Breaking Benjamin, ain't sure! Still, it all hits
right. Would recommend.
